Execute the following C# snippet that demonstrates IHttpHandlerFactory dynamic dispatch. Use the IHttpHandlerFactory signature from S3-2. The snippet should: (1) define a factory class implementing IHttpHandlerFactory; (2) inside GetHandler, use Type.GetType and Activator.CreateInstance to load a handler by name from the query string (e.g., ?handler=MyHandler); (3) include a fallback that returns a default handler when the type is not found. Run it and report the instantiation path and any exceptions for both the happy path and the fallback.

```csharp
using System;
using System.Web;

public class DynamicHandlerFactory : IHttpHandlerFactory
{
    public IHttpHandler GetHandler(HttpContext context, string requestType, string url, string pathTranslated)
    {
        string handlerName = context.Request.QueryString["handler"];
        if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(handlerName))
        {
            Type t = Type.GetType(handlerName, throwOnError: false);
            if (t != null && typeof(IHttpHandler).IsAssignableFrom(t))
                return (IHttpHandler)Activator.CreateInstance(t);
        }
        return new DefaultHandler();
    }
    public void ReleaseHandler(IHttpHandler handler) { }
}
public class DefaultHandler : IHttpHandler
{
    public bool IsReusable => false;
    public void ProcessRequest(HttpContext context) { context.Response.Write("default"); }
}
```

